# Stilgar · the naib of Sietch Tabr

Stilgar is the naib, the leader, of Sietch Tabr — the Fremen who takes in Paul and Jessica when they flee into the deep desert of Arrakis. He is a man of deep desert honor and shrewd leadership, the kind of authority that is earned among the Fremen rather than granted, rooted in the harsh law and loyalty of sietch life.

When Paul rises among the Fremen, Stilgar becomes Muad'Dib's fiercest disciple and a commander of the Fedaykin. The shelter he first offered becomes a discipleship; the man who took Paul in becomes the soldier who follows him.

Yet his devotion is shadowed by unease. Stilgar struggles as his friend Paul becomes a god to the Fremen, fearing what worship does both to the worshipped and to those who worship — sensing the cost hidden inside the adoration he himself helps create.

His emergence is natural: Stilgar is the embodied desert made flesh — the Fremen, the sietch, the soldier and the leader. He is not prescience nor messiah but a man of the sand, and through him the worm-haunted world of Arrakis takes a human shape that honor and dread can inhabit.
